reactor.core.queue.internal

Class MpscLinkedQueue<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • reactor.core.queue.internal.MpscLinkedQueue<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, Queue<E>

    public final class MpscLinkedQueue<E>
extends Object
implements Queue<E>
    A MultiProduceSingleConsumer impl. borrowed from Netty project which is also borrowing this from various sources. A lock-free concurrent single-consumer multi-producer Queue. It allows multiple producer threads to perform the following operations simultaneously:
    • offer(Object), add(Object), and addAll(Collection)
    • All other read-only operations:
      • contains(Object) and containsAll(Collection)
      • element(), peek()
      • size() and isEmpty()
      • iterator() (except Iterator.remove()
      • toArray() and toArray(Object[])
    .. while only one consumer thread is allowed to perform the following operations exclusively:
    • poll() and remove()
    • remove(Object), removeAll(Collection), and retainAll(Collection)
    • clear()
      • #

    The behavior of this implementation is undefined if you perform the operations for a consumer thread only from multiple threads.

    The initial implementation is based on:

    • Non-intrusive MPSC node based queue from 1024cores.net
    • AbstractNodeQueue from Akka
    and adopted padded head node changes from:
    • MpscPaddedQueue from RxJava
    data structure modified to avoid false sharing between head and tail Ref as per implementation of MpscLinkedQueue on JCTools project.
